import numpy as np
from scipy import stats

# Define the target materials
target_materials = ['aluiminium', 'gold', 'plastic']

# Generate uniformly distributed random values for target material
target_materials_rand = np.random.choice(target_materials, 25)

mean_cutoff_energy = 8.64
std_dev_cutoff_energy = np.sqrt(156)

# Generate synthetic data for numeric features using normal distribution
target_thicknesses_rand = stats.norm(loc=mean_thickness, scale=std_dev_thickness).rvs(25)
pulse_widths_rand = stats.norm(loc=mean_pulse_width, scale=std_dev_pulse_width).rvs(25)
energies_rand = stats.norm(loc=mean_energy, scale=std_dev_energy).rvs(25)
spot_sizes_rand = stats.norm(loc=mean_spot_size, scale=std_dev_spot_size).rvs(25)
intensities_rand = stats.norm(loc=mean_intensity, scale=std_dev_intensity).rvs(25)
powers_rand = stats.norm(loc=mean_power, scale=std_dev_power).rvs(25)

]
